cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with fact checking using a knowledge graph, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are likely categories. The paper also involves mining discriminative paths and evaluating veracity, which are related to data mining and machine learning, making cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval and link prediction, which are related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
